Package edu.cmu.cs214.hw5.framework.core.plugin.api

Interface ModelPlugin

  • public interface ModelPlugin
    This interface specifies the functionality which a prediction model plugin must provide to service the framework. A ModelPlugin generates an AugmentedDataSet by creating additional data points from a given RawDataSet through some form of extrapolation.

    It is expected, though not explicitly required, that the AugmentedDataSet returned from the call to applyModel(RawDataSet) will contain the input dataset unaltered as historical data, and forecast data consisting of future data points immediately following the last date of the input data.

    • Field Detail

      • TOTAL_PREDICTION_VALUES

        static final int TOTAL_PREDICTION_VALUES
        The total number of forecast data points.

        For simplicity, all model plugins are standardized to generate the same number of data points.

        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

    • Method Detail

      • getName

        java.lang.String getName()
        Returns the name of the plugin. This method is used by the framework to display the name of the plugin in the menu. The name of the plugin should reflect the model used to generate the forecast data.

        Note that the name of the plugin does not have to be unique from other plugins which may be present in the framework. However, identically named plugins will cause confusion for the user of the framework application, so it is recommended that plugin makers try to avoid potential name collisions (for example, by including a team name in the name of the plugin).

        Returns:
        the name of the plugin as it should appear in the framework menu.

      • setIncrement

        void setIncrement​(ModelPlugin.PredictionIncrement increment)
        Sets the time increment to be used between data points in the forecast.
        Parameters:
        increment - ModelPlugin.PredictionIncrement time increment between consecutive predictions.

      • applyModel

        AugmentedDataSet applyModel​(RawDataSet data)
        Returns the AugmentedDataSet containing the forecast and historical data for the given RawDataSet.

        The forecast data should be spaced according to the ModelPlugin.PredictionIncrement specified by the setIncrement(PredictionIncrement) function, which is guaranteed to have been called first. The number of predicted data points should equal TOTAL_PREDICTION_VALUES.

        Parameters:
        data - historical RawDataSet for projection.
        Returns:
        AugmentedDataSet containing the historical and forecast data of the given RawDataSet.
